articles.title: New captain Mitchell Marsh leads Australia to crushing win vs South Africa - Hindustan Times
articles.description: Marsh clubbed a T20 career-best 92 not out off 49 balls as Australia piled up 226 for six. South Africa were bowled out for 115. | Cricket
articles.content:
New captain Mitchell Marsh led a powerful Australian batting performance and set up a crushing 111-run win in the first Twenty20 international against South Africa at Kingsmead on Wednesday.
